19// The GraphProcessor takes a NodeProcessor, and applies it to each Node in the
20// Graph by calling NodeProcessor::Process on each Node.
21//
22// The GraphProcessor also keeps track of the current ProcessingState, and
23// passes this to the Process method.
24//
25// It expects a NodeProcessor class with:
26//
27// // A function that processes the graph before the nodes are walked.
28// void PreProcessGraph(Graph* graph);
29//
30// // A function that processes the graph after the nodes are walked.
31// void PostProcessGraph(Graph* graph);
32//
33// // A function that processes each basic block before its nodes are walked.
34// void PreProcessBasicBlock(BasicBlock* block);
35//
36// // Process methods for each Node type. The GraphProcessor switches over
37// // the Node's opcode, casts it to the appropriate FooNode, and dispatches
38// // to NodeProcessor::Process. It's then up to the NodeProcessor to provide
39// // either distinct Process methods per Node type, or using templates or
40// // overloading as appropriate to group node processing.
41// void Process(FooNode* node, const ProcessingState& state) {}
42//
43template <typename NodeProcessor, bool visit_identity_nodes = false>
44class GraphProcessor;
45
46enum class ProcessResult {
47 kContinue, // Process exited normally, and the following processors will be
48 // called on the node.
49 kRemove // Remove the current node from the graph (and do not call the
50 // following processors).
51};
52
53class ProcessingState {
54 public:
55 explicit ProcessingState(BlockConstIterator block_it,
56 NodeIterator* node_it = nullptr)
57 : block_it_(block_it), node_it_(node_it) {}
58
59 // Disallow copies, since the underlying frame states stay mutable.
60 ProcessingState(const ProcessingState&) = delete;
61 ProcessingState& operator=(const ProcessingState&) = delete;
62
63 BasicBlock* block() const { return *block_it_; }
64 BasicBlock* next_block() const { return *(block_it_ + 1); }
65
66 NodeIterator* node_it() const {
67 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(node_it_);
68 return node_it_;
69 }
70
71 private:
72 BlockConstIterator block_it_;
73 NodeIterator* node_it_;
74};
75
76template <typename NodeProcessor, bool visit_identity_nodes>
77class GraphProcessor {
78 public:
79 template <typename... Args>
80 explicit GraphProcessor(Args&&... args)
81 : node_processor_(std::forward<Args>(args)...) {}
82
83 void ProcessGraph(Graph* graph) {
84 graph_ = graph;
85
86 node_processor_.PreProcessGraph(graph);
87
88 auto process_constants = [&](auto& map) {
89 for (auto it = map.begin(); it != map.end();) {
90 ProcessResult result =
91 node_processor_.Process(it->second, GetCurrentState());
92 if (V8_UNLIKELY(result == ProcessResult::kRemove)) {
93 it = map.erase(it);
94 } else {
95 ++it;
96 }
97 }
98 };
99 process_constants(graph->constants());
100 process_constants(graph->root());
101 process_constants(graph->smi());
102 process_constants(graph->tagged_index());
103 process_constants(graph->int32());
104 process_constants(graph->uint32());
105 process_constants(graph->float64());
106 process_constants(graph->external_references());
107
108 for (block_it_ = graph->begin(); block_it_ != graph->end(); ++block_it_) {
109 BasicBlock* block = *block_it_;
110
111 node_processor_.PreProcessBasicBlock(block);
112
113 if (block->has_phi()) {
114 auto& phis = *block->phis();
115 for (auto it = phis.begin(); it != phis.end();) {
116 Phi* phi = *it;
117 ProcessResult result =
118 node_processor_.Process(phi, GetCurrentState());
119 if (V8_UNLIKELY(result == ProcessResult::kRemove)) {
120 it = phis.RemoveAt(it);
121 } else {
122 ++it;
123 }
124 }
125 }
126
127 for (node_it_ = block->nodes().begin();
128 node_it_ != block->nodes().end();) {
129 Node* node = *node_it_;
130 ProcessResult result = ProcessNodeBase(node, GetCurrentState());
131 if (V8_UNLIKELY(result == ProcessResult::kRemove)) {
132 node_it_ = block->nodes().RemoveAt(node_it_);
133 } else {
134 ++node_it_;
135 }
136 }
137
138 ProcessNodeBase(block->control_node(), GetCurrentState());
139 }
140
141 node_processor_.PostProcessGraph(graph);
142 }
143
144 NodeProcessor& node_processor() { return node_processor_; }
145 const NodeProcessor& node_processor() const { return node_processor_; }
146
147 private:
148 ProcessingState GetCurrentState() {
149 return ProcessingState(block_it_, &node_it_);
150 }
151
152 ProcessResult ProcessNodeBase(NodeBase* node, const ProcessingState& state) {
153 switch (node->opcode()) {
154#define CASE(OPCODE) \
155 case Opcode::k##OPCODE: \
156 if constexpr (!visit_identity_nodes && \
157 Opcode::k##OPCODE == Opcode::kIdentity) { \
158 return ProcessResult::kContinue; \
159 } \
160 PreProcess(node->Cast<OPCODE>(), state); \
161 return node_processor_.Process(node->Cast<OPCODE>(), state);
162
163 NODE_BASE_LIST(CASE)
164#undef CASE
165 }
166 }
167
168 void PreProcess(NodeBase* node, const ProcessingState& state) {}
169
170 NodeProcessor node_processor_;
171 Graph* graph_;
172 BlockConstIterator block_it_;
173 NodeIterator node_it_;
174};
175
176// A NodeProcessor that wraps multiple NodeProcessors, and forwards to each of
177// them iteratively.
178template <typename... Processors>
179class NodeMultiProcessor;
180
181template <>
182class NodeMultiProcessor<> {
183 public:
184 void PreProcessGraph(Graph* graph) {}
185 void PostProcessGraph(Graph* graph) {}
186 void PreProcessBasicBlock(BasicBlock* block) {}
187 ProcessResult Process(NodeBase* node, const ProcessingState& state) {
188 return ProcessResult::kContinue;
189 }
190};
191
192template <typename Processor, typename... Processors>
193class NodeMultiProcessor<Processor, Processors...>
194 : NodeMultiProcessor<Processors...> {
195 using Base = NodeMultiProcessor<Processors...>;
196
197 public:
198 template <typename... Args>
199 explicit NodeMultiProcessor(Processor&& processor, Args&&... processors)
200 : Base(std::forward<Args>(processors)...),
201 processor_(std::forward<Processor>(processor)) {}
202 template <typename... Args>
203 explicit NodeMultiProcessor(Args&&... processors)
204 : Base(std::forward<Args>(processors)...) {}
205
206 template <typename Node>
207 ProcessResult Process(Node* node, const ProcessingState& state) {
208 if (V8_UNLIKELY(processor_.Process(node, state) ==
209 ProcessResult::kRemove)) {
210 return ProcessResult::kRemove;
211 }
212 return Base::Process(node, state);
213 }
214 void PreProcessGraph(Graph* graph) {
215 processor_.PreProcessGraph(graph);
216 Base::PreProcessGraph(graph);
217 }
218 void PostProcessGraph(Graph* graph) {
219 // Post process in reverse order because that kind of makes sense.
220 Base::PostProcessGraph(graph);
221 processor_.PostProcessGraph(graph);
222 }
223 void PreProcessBasicBlock(BasicBlock* block) {
224 processor_.PreProcessBasicBlock(block);
225 Base::PreProcessBasicBlock(block);
226 }
227
228 private:
229 Processor processor_;
230};
231
232template <typename... Processors>
233using GraphMultiProcessor = GraphProcessor<NodeMultiProcessor<Processors...>>;
